{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"- (","kind":"text"},{"text":"void","preciseIdentifier":"c:v","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"mapView:","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNMapView","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMapView","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView"},{"text":" *) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"mapView","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"annotation:","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:Qoobjc(pl)MLNAnnotation","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"id<MLNAnnotation>"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"annotation"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"calloutAccessoryControlTapped:"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)UIControl","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UIControl"},{"kind":"text","text":" *) "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"control"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"mapView","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The map view containing the specified annotation."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"annotation","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The annotation whose accessory view was tapped."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"control","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The control that was tapped."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In a standard callout view, accessory views contain custom content and are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"positioned on either side of the annotation title text. If an accessory view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you specify is a descendant of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"UIControl","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" class, the map view calls this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method as a convenience whenever the user taps your view. You can use this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method to respond to taps and perform any actions associated with that control.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, if your control displays additional information about the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"annotation, you could use this method to present a modal panel with that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your custom accessory views are not descendants of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIControl"},{"type":"text","text":" class,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the map view does not call this method. If the annotation has a custom callout"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view via the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-mapView:calloutViewForAnnotation:"},{"type":"text","text":" method, you can specify the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"custom accessory views using the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCalloutView"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"leftAccessoryView"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rightAccessoryView"},{"type":"text","text":" properties."}]},{"anchor":"Related-examples","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Related examples"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Default callout usage, learn how to trigger an action when the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"standard callout bubble’s accessory control is tapped.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["